Instructions on building and running the SysMon example designs and scripts.

- KC705 with RJ45 Ethernet connection.
$ ipbb init sysmon
$ cd sysmon
$ ipbb add git https://github.com/jhegeman/ipbus-firmware -b ipbus_issue144
$ ipbb proj create vivado -t top_kc705_gmii_sysmon.dep kc705_sysmon ipbus-firmware:projects/example
$ cd proj/kc705_sysmon/
$ ipbb vivado make-project
$ ipbb vivado synth -j4 impl -j 4
$ ipbb vivado package

Now program the bit file into the FPGA.

$ ipbb vivado gendecoders
$ cd ../../src/ipbus-firmware/projects/example/scripts/
$ cp ../../../../../proj/kc705_sysmon/decoders/*.xml .
$ ./example_sysmon.py 192.168.200.16 example_sysmon_x7.xml

- VCU118 with RJ45 Ethernet connection.
$ ipbb init sysmon
$ cd sysmon
$ ipbb add git https://github.com/jhegeman/ipbus-firmware -b ipbus_issue144
$ ipbb proj create vivado -t top_vcu118_sgmii_sysmon.dep vcu118_sysmon ipbus-firmware:projects/example
$ cd proj/vcu118_sysmon/
$ ipbb vivado make-project
$ ipbb vivado synth -j4 impl -j 4
$ ipbb vivado package

Now program the bit file into the FPGA.

$ ipbb vivado gendecoders
$ cd ../../src/ipbus-firmware/projects/example/scripts/
$ cp ../../../../../proj/vcu118_sysmon/decoders/*.xml .
$ ./example_sysmon.py 192.168.200.17 example_sysmon_usp.xml

The output of the example script (for both examples) should show something like:
IPBus SysMon/XADC demo:
  temp   : 23.67 C
  vccint :  0.85 V
  vccaux :  1.79 V
  vrefp  :  0.00 V
  vrefn  :  0.00 V
  vccbram:  0.85 V
